05/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The bodies of six suspected illegal immigrants were found by fishermen in the delta of the Evros River, on the border between Greece and Turkey, authorities announced on Monday (January 4th). 
Authorities believe the group tried to cross the river in a boat, but died under circumstances that remain unclear. 
Two bodies were found on Monday, following four recovered at the weekend. 
None of the six carried identification. 
(DPA, CP - 04/01/10)
